<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FFED6A52F7EF947C1448B8C1" pageId="22" pageNumber="780" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFFED6A52F7EF947C1448B8C1" blockId="22.[2067,2662,465,893]" lastBlockId="22.[1443,2659,899,3496]" pageId="22" pageNumber="780">
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFED6A52F7EF947C16F5B970" authorityName="Temminck" authorityYear="1840" box="[2067,2293,549,578]" class="Liliopsida" family="Arecaceae" genus="Pipustrellus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Arecales" pageId="22" pageNumber="780" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tenuis">Pipustrellus tenuis</taxonomicName>
included 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFED6A52F67B947C1406B970" authorityName="Kitchener, Caputi &amp; Jones" authorityYear="1986" box="[2439,2566,549,578]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Pipistrellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="780" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="adamsi">P. adamsi</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFED6A52F5EB947C1673B95B" authorityName="Peters" authorityYear="1880" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Pipistrellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="780" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="angulatus">P. angulatus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFED6A52F77694091714B95B" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1920" box="[2186,2324,592,617]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Pipistrellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="780" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="collinus">P. collinus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFED6A52F6D6940917D3B95B" baseAuthorityName="Peters &amp; Doria" baseAuthorityYear="1881" box="[2346,2515,592,617]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Pipistrellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="780" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="papuanus">P. papuanus</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFED6A52F6169409145CB95B" authorityName=": Kitchener, Caputi &amp; B. Jones" authorityYear="1986" box="[2538,2652,592,617]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Pipistrellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="780" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="watts">P. watts</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFED6A52F7AA942116E7B9A3" authorityName="Koopman" authorityYear="1984" box="[2134,2279,632,657]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Pipistrellus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="780" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="westralis">P. westralis</taxonomicName>
, but all are recognized as distinct species based on morphology. Subspecies mimus was originally described as a distinct species but has generally been included under 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFED6A52F7019554176CB81C" authorityName="Temminck" authorityYear="1840" box="[2301,2412,781,814]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Vespertilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="780" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tenuis">P. tenuis</taxonomicName>
, although recent authors have chosen to continue to recognize mimus as a distinct species. As currently recognized, 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFED6A52F94895DA1920B896" authorityName="Temminck" authorityYear="1840" box="[1716,1824,899,932]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Vespertilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="780" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tenuis">P. tenuis</taxonomicName>
might represent a species complex, but additional research is needed. Recently extinct P. murray: has been included as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFFED6A52F63C95F3142CB8F9" authorityName="Temminck" authorityYear="1840" box="[2496,2604,938,971]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Vespertilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="780" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tenuis">P. tenuis</taxonomicName>
but is recognized as a separate species based on morphology. Six subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
